—(1) A person shall cease to be the tax representative for a non-resident taxpayer from when —
* the non-resident taxpayer ceases to be registered;
* the non-resident taxpayer replaces that person with a different tax representative under regulation 15 or 16;
* the Commissioners so direct under regulation 17;
* the person dies or becomes incapacitated or subject to an insolvency procedure;
* the person ceases to be eligible to be a tax representative;
* the person delivers to the Commissioners notification in writing that he withdraws as tax representative for the non-resident taxpayer; or
* the non-resident taxpayer delivers to the Commissioners notification in writing that he withdraws an appointment that they permitted but did not require.
* cease to be (or be treated as) the tax representative except in accordance with that regulation; or
* be permitted to withdraw under paragraph (1)(f) of this regulation.

A person who fails to comply with a requirement imposed on him by or under any of the following regulations shall be liable to a penalty of £250 for each such failure—
* regulation 2(1), 2(2), 2(3), 2(4) or 2(5) (form, manner, etc of notification about registrability);
* regulation 3(1), 3(5) or 3(10) (changes in particulars of notification about registrability);
* regulation 4(2) (notification of ceasing taxable activities);
* regulation 14(2) or 14(3) (notification by non resident taxpayer);
* regulation 19(1) or 19(2) (notification by tax representative).
